Although the closeness coefficients (
C ∗
) change slightly across scenarios, no scenario leads to a change in the ranking order. The largest variation is observed when the weight of Strengths is increased, which slightly improves the relative performance of A3 due to its high efficiency-related scores, but not enough to overtake A2 or A1. Figure 1 presents the sensitivity analysis of the TOPSIS results under different weighting scenarios for the four primary SWOT dimensions. The figure illustrates how variations in criterion weights influence the closeness coefficients of the three decision-making scenarios.
